  "markdown_content": "\n## Executive Summary\n\nUser requested adding Notion MCP server via SSE endpoint. Manus clarified that MCP server configuration is a platform-level operation outside session scope and provided step-by-step guidance for proper configuration through the Manus settings interface.\n\n\n## Context & Intent\n\nUser attempted to configure MCP server integration from within session chat\n\n\n## What Was Done\n\nManus provided clear explanation of MCP configuration scope limitations and detailed procedural guidance\n\n\n## Outputs Produced\n\n- [procedural_guide] MCP Server Configuration Steps — Step-by-step instructions for adding Notion MCP server through settings interface\n\n## Key Decisions & Validations\n\n- Clarified that MCP server configuration is platform-level, not session-level operation\n\n## Lessons Learned\n\nWorked well:\n\n- Clear scope boundary communication\n- Provided actionable alternative solution\nDiscoveries:\n\n- Notion MCP server already configured in current environment\n\n## Challenges & Blockers\n\n- Session-level limitations for platform configuration changes\n\n## Open Questions\n\n- Whether existing Notion MCP server is functioning correctly\n- If duplicate configuration or endpoint update is needed\n\n## Next Steps\n\n- User to access Manus settings interface for MCP configuration\n- Authenticate with Notion account if required\n- Run diagnostic on existing Notion MCP if connection issues persist\n---\nUID: 9dt2qNPVmQAVLITBDBZTbE | Model: claude-sonnet-4-20250514 | Cost: $0.0102\n"
